  "text": "In order to construct the networks, we need to define their nodes and edges. Nodes are local optima and edges represent escape probabilities. Local optima networks for neutral landscapes have been studied before by Verel et al. [CITATION_1] ; we borrow their notation and definitions, but name a sequence of connected solutions with the same fitness as plateaus rather than as neutral networks, to avoid confusion with the local optima network terminology.",
